items.name: QteaMix 通用Q版模型
items.description:
我重新调整了此前Omega版的画风以保持Qtea的一致性，仍然能直出大图，以及稳定的Q版人物。已经更换了上传的文件以及展示图。

上传的确实是原图，不知为何检测不到生成数据，但所用提示词与此前的展示图完全一致。

推荐的负面为verybadimagenegative_v1.3

I adjusted the art style of the Omega version to maintain the consistency of Qtea. It can still output large pictures and stable chibi style. I have replaced the uploaded files and display pictures. The uploaded files are indeed the original pictures. I don’t know why the generated data cannot be detected, but the prompts used are completely consistent with the previous display pictures.

Negative prompt: verybadimagenegative_v1.3

6.20

————————————————————————————————————

Omega，这是QteaMix的最终一个版本，是模型的升级。以新素材训练融合引入、修正而来。同样可以适应多种分辨率（甚至可到1280*1280）多种比例，同时保有足够的提示词理解能力。能够简单的通过1boy获得男性。

与此前的版本相比，Omega的线条更加明显，并消除了多余的无意义高光，更加扁平化，对于负面提示词要求不高，即使在不使用任何负面的情况下也比过去的版本表现更好。

同时，QteaMix也足以作为合格的训练底模，适合chibi风格的训练集，考虑到模型中的垃圾数据对于出图结果没有影响，已将其精简，并只上传半精度版本。

以上。

若非更喜欢旧版本画风，推荐下载omega版。

QteaMix已完成，将不会再有更新。

Omega, this is the final version of QteaMix, which is an upgrade of the model. It is trained on new materials and fused with corrections. It can also adapt to various resolutions (even up to 1280*1280) and ratios while maintaining sufficient understanding of prompt words. It can easily generate male characters through 1boy.

Compared with previous versions, Omega’s lines are more prominent and unnecessary highlights have been eliminated. It is more flattened and requires less negative prompt words. Even without any negative prompts, it performs better than previous versions.

At the same time, QteaMix can also serve as a qualified training bottom model for chibi-style training sets. Considering that the garbage data in the model has no effect on the output results, it has been streamlined and only half-precision versions have been uploaded.

That’s all.

If you prefer the old version’s style, it is recommended to download Omega version.

QteaMix is now complete and will not be updated anymore

————————————————————————————————————

注意：omicron并不是模型的升级迭代，而应该看作另一个模型。

关于omicron，相比gamma版更加稳定，不容易脱Q，并且能适应更多分辨率，但代价是失去了1boy+male出男性的能力，具体风格差异请参照对比图。

特别说明，omicron在使用 easynegative或verybadimagenegative_v1.3时呈现出两种不同的风格，前者具有更精致的色调，后者具有更显眼的线条，一般来说，使用verybadimagenegative_v1.3的风格会更加适合Q版，请自行尝试。

Note: Omicron is not an upgrade iteration of the model, but should be seen as another model.

Regarding omicron, it is more stable than the gamma version, not easy to get off Q, and can adapt to more resolutions, but at the cost of losing the ability of 1boy + male to produce men, please refer to the comparison chart for specific style differences.

In particular, omicron presents two different styles when using easynegative or verybadimagenegative_v1.3, the former has a more delicate tone, the latter has more prominent lines, in general, using the style of verybadimagenegative_v1.3 will be more suitable for the Q version, please try it yourself.

————————————————————————————————————

四元融合Q版通用模型，具有更少细节与更扁平风格，适应表情素材、立牌、人物Q版化，较为泛用。通常加“chibi”就能简单的达成，甚至不加也可以。推荐原始分辨率不超过960

items.name: Style Asian Less
items.description:
Follow me to make sure you see new styles, poses and Nobodys when I post them. Things move fast on this site, it's easy to miss.

Most of the recent, good, training has been using anime and models trained on asian people and it's culture. Nothing wrong with that, it's great that the community and fine-tunning continues to grow. But those models are mixed in with almost everything now, sometimes it might be difficult to get results that don't have asian or anime influence. This embedding aims to assist with that. It can even change anime characters (though that wasn't the intended purpose).

I first created this when trying to make preview images for my South of the Border Style embedding. I was trying to get south american people and culture, but there was a lot of asian culture leaking into the generated images. This embedding fixed that. So it doesn't specifically race-swap asian to white-caucasian, it just removes asian so your prompts can be more effective with whatever other race or culture you're trying to portray.

How to use:
Use the negative prompt primarily, then use the positive prompts only if you need the additional help. There are 3 files to download.

  • Asian-Less-Neg: Use this one, place in your negative prompt at strength of 1.0

  • Asian-Less: Only use this in the positive prompt if you need the extra strength. On an asian-specific model for example.

  • Asian-Less-Toon: Only use this in the positive prompt if you need to remove anime-like features in illustrations.

Again, this isn't meant to race-swap, but to help get other race and/or cultures in your image generation without the influence of the asian image training. But like all models, the intended use and what you do with it are separate matters.

Do you have requests? I've been putting in many more hours lately with this. That's my problem, not yours. But if you'd like to tip me, buy me a beer. Beer encourages me to ignore work and make AI models instead. Tip and make a request. I'll give it a shot if I can. Here at Ko-Fi

items.name: Dune/Demobaza Inspired Outfit by milkomt
items.description:
☿ This Lora will dress up your character in an outfit inspired by Dune 2021 and Demobaza clothing!

☿ Using:

  • Works best on Lora 1.0 weight, but also in the 0.75-1.35 range, creating more "inspired" outfits at low weight and more "tough" outfits at high weight.

  • The activation tag is demo_baza, additionally use demo_boots, demo_gloves, demo_shoulder_pads, demo_sleeve to invoke clothing elements

  • Also the collar cover mouth, scarf, veil and wind blowing give good results.

  • Other elements like clothing types, hairstyles, poses, colors, backgrounds etc work as usual.

My favorite format for this Lora:

Prompt: demo_baza, a 1girl running in a desert, long dress, long massive sleeve, wind blowing long red hair, wind blowing long veil <lora:demo_baza:1>

Negatives: photo, real, (worst quality, low quality:1.4), (easynegative:1.2), (sketch:1.2), (logo, text, signature, link, artstation, patreon, deviantart:1.2), 3d, render

☿ Features:

  • Likes to draw girls, brunettes, and slicked back hair, add in negatives or push the weight of other prompts

  • Draws men too, mostly in studio "curvy" poses, but they are rendered in other poses without trouble

  • Doesn't shit your style.

  • Draws realism and anime, use real, photo, anime, realistic tags in the right fields to create or decrease an effect

items.name: Satori (Pokémon) LoRA
items.description:
What? Isn't the right time for this because Ash's farewell as a protagonist of the anime was a short time ago? Oh Well... you will overcome this someday.

ANYWAY! Despite being released soon after, this model isn't related to Kirisuna (believe me), this one is an older idea. A little context for those who are confused (Links below may have "some" NSFW content, proceed with caution), this is also credits for the idea.

▼▼▼CONTEXT STARTS HERE▼▼▼

This is obviously the fusion of Ash Ketchum and Dawn. Why? Good question... But this is more common than you think. Some people believe that Dawn has the best synergy with Ash compared to all other companions because they have similar personalities, as if Dawn were Ash's coordinator counterpart and this is more or less recognized in Pokémon Journeys with Alt. Ash and Alt. Dawn switching roles. Perhaps that's the reason. I honestly never saw them that way, as Dawn always struck me as too "feminine" and "vain with looks" to be compared to Ash's "sloppy" personality. But if it serves as an excuse to merge the two, who am I to say the opposite?

The oldest example on the internet about this idea is from 2020 with TSFSingularity's web comic. The story is about Mewtwo suddenly using its powers to merge Ash and Dawn, in this version Ash is in control of the body while Dawn's mind can do nothing but to experience Ash's actions. It's an interesting comic at first but becomes lame in the second half because just becomes a standard Ash and Dawn hentai with the fusion losing the story focus.

However, according to TSFSingularity, the idea is even older and comes from an art of Rhaokja. I never found this art, so I don't know how it is and its date.

Some time later, hide1001 came up with the same idea. hide1001's gallery is focused on fusions, not always the most unorthodox ones, the majority are pretty normal with female-female fusions, but some examples between Ash and Dawn appeared here and there but it had its first main role in the 2021 "comic" with the rough translate title "Beware of Hex Maniac when exploring the ruins", is a story using screenshots from the game Koikatsu! and it's about Ash and Dawn getting lost in the ruins of a city, they end finding a crazy Hex Maniac who casts a spell on them that consequently merges their bodies creating a new entity called "Satori", hence the name (Satoshi + Hikari. I have no idea how "Ash" and "Dawn" would be), unlike TSFSingularity's version, Satori is apparently a combination of their personalities rather than one of them being in control.

The idea is interesting but unfortunately all the dialogues are in Japanese. A version for western audience was posted on hide1001's deviantart, but without the dialogues, which doesn't help much. Google translator did a mediocre job for me to understand the context: Sounds like a story of Ash promising to protect Dawn, but ends up failing when they find the Hex Maniac and that leads the two ending in this situation with their bodies merging into this new person... A bit tragic, isn't it? Or a bit Jojolion.

I don't know if hide1001 was directly inspired by the TSFSingularity version, but sounds like it because both versions of "Satori" are very similar physically, with the difference that the TSFSingularity version has Dawn's blue eyes while hide1001's version has Ash's brown eyes, the latter is a bit more equal in traits distribution between Ash and Dawn.

But overall it's pretty much a slight tan Dawn with lines on her cheeks, spiky locks on the sides of the hair that are reminiscent of Ash's hair and is herm (The big breasts apparently came as a fusion "boost" in both cases). Both versions are technically that physically.

▲▲▲CONTEXT ENDS HERE▲▲▲

Now to what really matters. I make it clear that this model is pretty bad, the worst I've done so far. There weren't enough resources for the character, even trying to complement it with some Dawn and Ash artworks for at least the clothes to be consistent. The result was bad no matter how many repeats and epochs I put in.

The only reason I decided to post this model is because it becomes much more acceptable if you put large steps to generate the image. A few steps like 20~30 will inevitably always generate a image with messy face. On the other hand, you don't need to lower the weight much, 0.9 already generates images in good quality, but maybe you have to lower it a little more if you want a better variation on scenarios (Putting "hxruins" in the negative prompt also helps).

"ash's cap" leaves Satori's hair the way it should be, but without the hat the image can sometimes misinterpret the spiky hair as some sort of "french braid". "ash's cheek marks" technically should make the cheek marks show up, but instead it just makes the face look messy, the results are better without it.

If I find a solution to improve this model, maybe I'll bring a V2, but don't keep expectations. For now, if you can, show some love for our little... Girl...? Boy...? Our little trainer and coordinator from Pokémon world!

items.description:
If you make some cool images, please consider sharing them, and leaving a review. That is why I make these. :)

After the success retraining Dolph, I decided to try my luck with a new character, before I retrain Red-Nosed Raider. I really like Highwire this season, and wanted to see if I could make a character who has 3 different outfits in 1 LORA.

She came out pretty swell I think. Her glasses are kinda wonky, but it gets close enough I think. Maybe this can be smoothed out later. If you weigh them higher they'll turn out better, probably with inpainting they can turn out perfect.

Supports Wolf Version and Bunny version, with hood up and down.

You can get good results with 1 image, but I generate 5 and pick the best. That's pretty much what I do with all models, but just my habit. Can be clothed, nude, etc. LORA strength between 0.8 - 1.0 is ok from my tests.

You can add texting, holding cellphone, cellphone, for texting, or you can do holding cellphone, selfie, for taking a selfie.

Other tags, like Contrail, Skydiving, Glider, etc. You can specify different views with Front View, 3/4 View, Side View, 3/4 Rear View, or Rear View.

Lots of fun to be had. :)

Also highly recommend EasyNegative which my sample images are using.

If you get bad looking faces at lower resolutions try inpainting only the face at higher resolution or using hires fix. This is especially important for Ayane since at lower resolutions the red in her pupils will bleed into her eyes and she'll look super baked.

items.name: Debi Mazar
items.description:
follow me on Instagram, Youtube, Patreon and my website.

Debi Mazar

Suggested Weight: 0.7-1.2

Suggested prompts

  • photo of young d381m4z4r with a-line bob haircut and makeup as a [something], detailed face, skin texture, sharp focus, light bokeh

  • most of the training was from recent images, so to get a younger version add "young" to positive prompts, and try adding "old" and "wrinkles" and etc to the negative prompt

  • Works very well for closeup portraits without inpainting

Training

  • trained on ~24 images

  • Learning Rate: 0.005:1000, 0.001:2000, 0.0001:5000, 0.00005

  • Total Steps: 15,000

  • Batch Size: 1

  • Gradient Steps: 1

items.name: John Fetterman
items.description:
follow me on Instagram, Youtube, Patreon and my website.

John Fetterman

Suggested Weight: 0.7-1.0

Suggested prompts

  • realistic portrait photo of j0hnf3tt3rm4n taken with a hasselblad h6d-400c 1.4, bald

  • This is not an easy embedding to use, and takes lots of practice, trial and error

  • it is VERY easy to get a weird "shrink wrapped" look with the skin

  • Inpainting is almost necessary (every example image you see here was created with inpainting)

  • All that said, with the right prompts, model and inpainting it's very possible to create lots of variations

Training

  • trained on ~12 images

  • Learning Rate: 0.005:1000, 0.001:2000, 0.0001:5000, 0.00005

  • Total Steps: 15,000

  • Batch Size: 1

  • Gradient Steps: 1

items.name: Shadow97's Particle
items.description:
This is a rather old model of mine, so it might be faulty in some aspects. Most notably, it sometimes produces nonsensical faces and creates textures where they shouldn't be, but you should be fine as long as you use recommended settings.

Sampler: DPM++ 2M Karras, DPM++ SDE Karras

Steps: 20+

CFG Scale: Anywhere between 4 to 11, beyond that I did not test, but I doubt you'd be using values outside of that bracket anyway. Lower scale values seem to be more "creative" at the cost of producing more muted colors. Also, higher CFG scale values tend to produce aforementioned errors more often (for instance, on Euler a with 20 steps and no hires.fix)

Hires.fix: on, upscaler either any of the Latents or R-ESRGAN 4x of your taste. Latent is more creative, R-ESRGAN is less prone to nonsense generations. Use denoise strength in the range of 0.55 to 0.75 for Latent and 0.3 to 0.75 for R-ESRGAN.

Clip Skip: 1 or 2, the effect is similar to CFG Scale with 1 being more creative and 2 having deeper contrast and more popping colors (all example images made with Clip Skip 2).

VAE: the one from the base SD 1.5 model. I didn't bake it in just in case you want to use something else with the model.
